{
  "stem": "22447.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 76,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So you didn't go out, you had the night's sleep, and you helped the cook in the morning make breakfast and making dinner during the day time.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 77,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So he come round to me, says, would you like to have off Friday night to Saturday morning or Saturday morning to Sunday morning?",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 77,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Of course, we had the Sabbath, so they said you can have the option which one.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 77,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It's not much difference.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 77,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I'm not going anywhere.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 77,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So I said, all right, I'll go for Saturday morning until Sunday.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 77,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "At least I have all day Saturday off.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 77,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we were sleeping on the beaches at the time because the-- the invasion scare was at its height.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 77,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And also the intelligence people, they used to do these reconnaissance visits, the RAF, and they noticed in the [INAUDIBLE], the Calais area, there was hundreds of barges.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 77,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And nobody could work it out.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 77,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Why do they need the barges?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 77,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Why did the Germans need the barges?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 77,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They're not saving them up like dinky toys.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 77,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And they couldn't work it out.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 77,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And then one Sunday morning, I was helping the cook.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 77,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "An officer come in, he said, what are you doing?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 77,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I said, I'm helping the cook making breakfast.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 77,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "He said, if you don't go out there, the Germans will have you for breakfast.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 77,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "He said, there's an inviting going on out there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 77,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "So I said, well, how they getting on?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 77,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] He said, get out there quick.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 77,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "So I went out, so a loud cheer went up.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 77,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "England's last hope's arrived.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 77,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] So anyway, this was 7 o'clock in the morning.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 77,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "At 9:00-- at 9 o'clock in the morning, the all clear went so we left the dugouts on the coast, and we-- we went back.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
